                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d325">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 837.00/514.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 1233.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-12-04">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">December</hi> 4, 1911</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: With reference to my dispatch No. 1225 of the 1st
                    instant [etc.] I have the honor to report that a bill signed by Messrs. Freyre
                    Andrade, González Lanuza and other Conservative members has now been introduced
                    in the lower House of Congress to repeal in their entirety the civil service law
                    drafted by the late Provisional Government and the complementary and
                    promulgatory act of January 18, 1911.</p>
                <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hugh S. Gibson</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
